cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) because it deals with identifying users based on their web transactions, which is a security concern. It could also belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with privacy and user profiling. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with analyzing web traffic data. It could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses one-class classification techniques to profile users. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with extracting features from web transactions.
